_meanings:
{@--1@} To be, exist,
abide, remain, subsist, stay; {#idaM me#}
{#manasi vartate#} <ls>Ś. 1</ls>; {#atra vizaye'smAkaM#}
{#mahatkutUhalaM vartate#} <ls>Pt. 1</ls>;  
{#marAlakulanAyakaH kaTaya re kaTaM vartatAM#} <ls>Bv. 1. 3</ls>; often
used merely as a copula;  
{#atItya harito harIMSca vaMrtate vAjinaH#}
<ls>Ś. 1.</ls>

{@--3@} To 
happen, take place, occur, come to pass;
{#sItAdevyAH kiM vfttamityasti kAcitpravfttiH#}
<ls>U. 2</ls>; {#sAyaM saMprati vartate paTika re#} 
{#sTAnAMtaraM gamyatAM#} <ls>Subhāṣ.</ls> ‘now it is
evening’ &c.; <ls>Ś. Til. 6</ls>; <ls>Bg. 5. 26.</ls>

{@--4@} To move on, proceed in regular
course; {#sarvaTA vartate yajYaH#} <ls>Ms. 2. 15</ls>;
{#nirvyAjamijyA vavfte#} <ls>Bk. 2. 37</ls>;  
<ls>R. 12. 56.</ls>

{@--6@} To turn, roll on, 
revolve; {#yAvadiyaM lokayAtrA vartate#}  
<ls>Ve. 3.</ls>

{@--7@} To occupy or engage oneself,
be occupied or engaged in, set about
(with loc); {#BagavAn kASyapaH SASvate#}
{#brahmaRi vartate#} <ls>Ś. 1</ls>; {#itaro dahane#} 
{#svakarmaRAM vavfte jYAnamayena vAhninA#} <ls>R. 8. 20</ls>;
<ls>Ms. 8. 346</ls>; <ls>Bg. 3. 22.</ls>

{@--8@} To act,
behave, conduct or demean oneself
towards, do, perform, practise
(usually with <ab>loc.</ab> or by itself);
{#Aryo'smin vinayena vartatAM#} <ls>U. 6</ls>;
{#kavirnisargasOhfdena Baratezu vartamAnaH#}  
<ls>Māl. 1</ls>; {#OdAsInyena vartituM#} <ls>R. 10. 25</ls>;
{#mitravanmayyavartizwa#} <ls>Dk.</ls>; <ls>Ms. 7. 104</ls>,
<ls n="Ms.">8. 173</ls>, <ls n="Ms.">11. 30</ls>.

{@--10@} To act up to, abide by, 

follow, {#tadaSakyAraMBAduparamya mAturmate#} 
{#vartasva#} <ls>Dk.</ls>

{@--11@} To have the sense of,
signify, be used in the sense of;
{#puzyasamIpasTe caMdramasi puzyaSabdo vartate#}
<ls>Mbh.</ls> on <ls>P. IV. 2. 3</ls> (often used
in lexicons in this sense).

{@--12@} To
tend or conduce to (with. <ab>dat.</ab>);
{#putreRa kiM PalaM yo vE pitfduHKAya vartate#}.

{@--2@} To cause to move or turn round,
cause to revolve; {#jyotIMzi vartayati ca#}
{#praviBaktaraSmiH#} <ls>Ś. 7. 6.</ls>

{@--3@} To 
brandish, flourish, whirl round;  
<ls>Bk. 15. 37.</ls>

{@--5@} To perform, 
discharge, attend or look to;  
{#soDikAramaBikaH kulocitaM ka Scana#} 
{#svayamavartayatsamAH#} <ls>R. 19. 4</ls>; <ls>Mv. 3. 23.</ls>

{@--7@} To live
on, subsist; {#rAmopi saha vEdehyA vane#} 
{#vanyena vartayan#} <ls>R. 12. 80</ls>; sometimes
<ab>Atm.</ab> also; {#madasiktamuKErmfgADipaH#} 
{#kariBirvartayate svayaM hatEH#} <ls>Ki. 2. 18.</ls>
